messageBody:
Brett,

The next one is a representation of a fraction and has two fields and
validation. After that I have a U.S. Social Security Number with three
fields and quite a significant quantity of domain rules and validation in
it.

The SSN object is part of another collection called ClassicDomainObjects:

http://github.com/simonpeter/ClassicDomainObjects

ClassicDomainObjects is still in its early phase, but it is my intention to
work the objects in the same comprehensive fashion as BinaryDigit and
Fraction.

Hope this helps.

Simon
